<br>
I get hit a good bit while quadding (and not by accident, either).  I do it on purpose so I can occasionally work on bind wound, but primarily to get my Defense and Dodge skills up.<br>
<br>
All that's well and good, but there's a problem, and it's getting worse with each passing level :<br>
<br>
At level 43, my <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Defense</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> skill is only 45 and has been stuck at that same amount since the mid-20s (if I had to guess as to when it got stuck).  It seems very interesting to me that it's stuck exactly 100 points below the Defense cap of 145, but I'm not sure if that's of any significance or not.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, my <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Offense</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> skill is at 124.  I was always under the impression that Offense skill-ups were primarily (but not entirely) related to melee attacking, but the only melee skill I've ever used is piercing, which is at a skill of 18.  As you can tell by that number, I've rarely used melee attacks.<br>
<br>
My Dodge skill, which I got at.... level 22 (?) has already surpassed my defense skill by far, and is at 74.<br>
<br>
Remember that I said I got hit a lot on purpose while quadding?  Well, guess which skill has been going up like crazy when I get hit like that...  Yep, my <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>OFFENSE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> skill, which explains the numbers.  Dodge has been going up as well, but NO Defense skill-ups.  Zilch.  Nada.<br>
<br>
To me, this is clearly broken or bugged, and it's going to cause me some major problems if they don't fix it real soon.  I level like a madman, and I'll be facing MUCH tougher mobs very soon.<br>
<br>
If I had to hazard a guess (and this is strictly a shot in the dark), I'd say that my Defense skill somehow got broken or reversed with my Offense skill when I trained the Dodge skill, since Defense has been stuck since somewhere in my 20s, and that's when I trained Dodge.  I also got LoY at around that same time, too.<br>
<br>
Anyone else have any similar observations or an explanation as to why this is happening?  Is Defense possibly put on hold until Dodge is capped?  I sure don't remember that happening before, but I levelled my last wizzy to 50 before Kunark came out, so that was a long time ago.<br>
<br>
I'm stumped... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 2573<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/03 11:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Defense broken?  Or reversed with Offense?</span><hr size=1> Mine were all maxed at 50 and I didn't notice anything strange. The skill increases for those are just random and require blue mobs. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
